tion-pill-access-telehealth-mail-rcna343148</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/health/womens-health/appeals-court-blocks-abortion-pill-access-telehealth-mail-rcna343148</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260501-mifepristone-pills-vsb-1756-315ef0.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Charlie Riedel</media:credit><media:text type="plain">A patient prepares to take the first of two combination pills, mifepristone.</media:text><media:description type="plain">A patient prepares to take the first of two combination pills, mifepristone, for a medication abortion during a visit to a clinic in Kansas City, Kan., Oct. 12, 2022.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260501-mifepristone-pills-vsb-1756-315ef0.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Fri, 01 May 2026 22:23:19 GMT</pubDate><title>Appeals court blocks access to abortion pills via telehealth and mail nationwide</title><updateDate>Fri, 01 May 2026 23:15:41 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Natasha Korecki</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Fri, 01 May 2026 19:59:44 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Illinois Gov. JB Pritzker may be a billionaire, but should the Democrat run for president in 2028, he may for the first time accept fundraising dollars, NBC News has learned</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2028-election/billionaire-illinois-gov-jb-pritzker-not-fully-self-finance-2028-run-rcna343122</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2028-election/billionaire-illinois-gov-jb-pritzker-not-fully-self-finance-2028-run-rcna343122</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260430-Pritzker-vsb-1702-6609fa.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Angelina Katsanis</media:credit><media:text type="plain">J.B. Pritzker</media:text><media:description type="plain">Illinois Gov. J.B. Pritzker speaks at the National Action Network Convention in New York, on April 9.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260430-Pritzker-vsb-1702-6609fa.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Fri, 01 May 2026 19:59:44 GMT</pubDate><title>Billionaire Illinois Gov. JB Pritzker explores something new in a 2028 run: Raising money</title><updateDate>Fri, 01 May 2026 21:36:59 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Jane C. Timm </dc:creator><dc:contributor>Rebecca Shabad</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>Adam Edelman</dc:contributor><dateTimeWritten>Fri, 01 May 2026 19:09:48 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Alabama Gov. Kay Ivey called legislators into a special session Friday and asked them to reschedule the state&#39;s midterm primaries, in hopes that pushing those elections back will give them time to re-install congressional maps that had been blocked in court before a landmark Supreme Court ruling changed the landscape around race and redistricting this week</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/alabama-governor-calls-special-session-move-primaries-redistricting-ge-rcna343125</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/alabama-governor-calls-special-session-move-primaries-redistricting-ge-rcna343125</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260501-Kay-Ivey-gk-06cf66.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1668" width="2500"><media:credit>Vasha Hunt</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Kay Ivey</media:text><media:description type="plain">Alabama Gov. Kay Ivey in 2023, in Troy, Ala.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260501-Brian-Kemp-gk-57ae10.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Brynn Anderson</media:credit><media:text type="plain">State of the State Georgia</media:text><media:description type="plain">Alabama Gov. Kay Ivey in 2023, in Troy, Ala.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260501-Kay-Ivey-gk-06cf66.jpg" height="1668" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Fri, 01 May 2026 19:09:48 GMT</pubDate><title>Alabama governor calls special session to move primaries for redistricting, while Georgia passes</title><updateDate>Fri, 01 May 2026 19:09:48 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Alexandra Marquez</dc:creator><dc:contributor>Monica Alba</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>Bridget Bowman</dc:contributor><dateTimeWritten>Fri, 01 May 2026 13:58:22 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Former President Joe Biden on Friday backed former Atlanta mayor Keisha Lance Bottoms&#39; campaign for governor in Georgia, his first endorsement since leaving office last year.&#34;I&#39;ve known her for a long time, and she&#39;s something special,&#34; Biden said in a video backing the former mayor, who served as a senior adviser in the Biden administration</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/biden-endorses-keisha-lance-bottoms-georgia-governor-rcna343057</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/biden-endorses-keisha-lance-bottoms-georgia-governor-rcna343057</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260501-Keisha-Lance-Bottoms-Biden-ch-0918-d86973.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="800" width="1200"><media:credit>Getty Images</media:credit><media:text type="plain">A split composite of Joe Biden and Keisha Lance Bottoms.</media:text><media:descript